rules: Rule1: Either the road has a blockage or it is not the case that power has an outage.
Rule2: Under the condition that supply has a delivery, the road does not have a blockage.
Rule3: Supply has a delivery or aid has an arrival.
Rule4: Whenever aid has an arrival, it follows that the road does not have a blockage.
Rule5: If the tool has a battery, then if the furniture has an anchor, the community has safety.
Rule6: The animal has a shelter, or if the food has a stockpile, then the tool has a battery.
Rule7: If the phenomenon has a warning, then the animal does not have a shelter.
Rule8: Either the phenomenon has a warning or the forecast has accuracy.
Rule9: Provided that the forecast has accuracy, the animal does not have a shelter.
Rule10: Under the condition that the team has readiness, it follows that the animal does not have a shelter.
Rule11: If communication has a failure, then power has an outage.
Rule12: Communication has a failure, or if the team does not have readiness, then the government has an alert.
facts: Fact1: The furniture has an anchor.
Fact2: The food has a stockpile.
Fact3: The government does not have an alert.
